    "body": "### Problem\n\nSince ef94fb6, ephemeral inline virt-text stopped being rendered. As far as I could understand, that's because `w_buffer->b_virt_text_inline` (count of inline virt text extmarks in a buffer) doesn't get incremented if the `opts` passed to `nvim_buf_set_extmark()` contain `ephemeral = true` and `virt_text_pos = 'inline'`. However, it does get incremented if the extmark is not ephemeral, because in this case `extmark_set()` is invoked, which is the only place that increments said counter.\r\n\r\nhttps://github.com/neovim/neovim/blob/b263c73b083e43761386d46d62524ea104d7abbd/src/nvim/api/extmark.c#L823-L837\r\n\r\nWhen `ephemeral = true` and `virt_text_pos = inline`:\r\n- `nvim_buf_set_extmark()` -> `decor_add_ephemeral()` -> `decor_add()` -> doesn't increment the counter -> virt-text doesn't get rendered\r\n\r\nWhen `ephemeral = false` and `virt_text_pos = inline`:\r\n- `nvim_buf_set_extmark()` -> `extmark_set()` -> increments the counter -> virt-text gets rendered\r\n\r\nI'd be more than happy to try to fix it in a PR, but I am not sure where the counter should be incremented.\n\n### Steps to reproduce\n\nnvim --clean\r\n:e file.txt\r\n:lua local ns = vim.api.nvim_create_namespace('something'); vim.api.nvim_set_decoration_provider(ns, { on_line = function() vim.api.nvim_buf_set_extmark(0, ns, 0, 0, { virt_text = { { 'thing', 'Comment' } }, virt_text_pos = 'inline', hl_mode = 'combine', ephemeral = true }) end });\n\n### Expected behavior\n\nEphemeral inline virt-text should be rendered correctly. In the example above, the word `thing` should be rendered at row 0 col 0 on each line draw.\n\n### Neovim version (nvim -v)\n\n0.10.0 commit b263c73\n\n### Vim (not Nvim) behaves the same?\n\nn/a\n\n### Operating system/version\n\nArch Linux 6.4.11-arch1-1 BTW\n\n### Terminal name/version\n\nkitty 0.29.2\n\n### $TERM environment variable\n\nxterm-kitty\n\n### Installation\n\nAUR (neovim-git)",
