            "body": "Sooo... What's the plan? Are they getting fixed or removed? No pressure. Just asking because I'm trying to find a workaround to get the same effect.\r\n\r\nAlso, here are the workarounds I've come up with so far (any help would be appreciated):\r\n- Add an empty non-ephemeral inline extmark to the buffer to increment the counter so that other ephemeral inline virt-text extmarks get rendered\r\n\r\nOr\r\n\r\n- Use non-ephemeral extmarks combined with the `virtualedit` option to set the cursor position manually, to mimic the behavior of ephemeral inline extmarks.",
